<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-07-0318 </DOCNO><TEXT>It is argued that, in order to obtain optimum competition with minimumregulation in a privatised electricity supply industry, there shouldbe an independent non-profit transmission company, owned by the distributioncompanies and free to buy electricity in an expanded market. Examplesof policy and practice overseas are included and the relative meritsof different possible methods of organising the transmission companyare considered.</TEXT></DOC>